caption: I really enjoyed everything about this spot. Bae and I went during dinner hours on a A Sunday, which was around 730pm. They also have a brunch day party situation earlier in the day. The DJ was playing great music but it wasn’t too loud that I couldn’t converse with Bae. The ambiance was nice and elegant with dim lights. Their unisex bathroom is very clean. The food menu wasn’t overwhelming it was simple but full of great options. We drank a old fashion with our choice of Whiskey and had a bottle of Merlot and we were able to take the rest home. Service was superb and I’m looking forward to coming back, but hopefully for brunch

While visiting Washington DC we were referred to The Park restaurant. At first we were intimated by the guests’ attire at the door and we weren’t sure if we were going to be allowed inside because we didn’t have any reservations and of course I had forgotten my ID. Nevertheless, they confirmed my identity and once inside we received nothing but AMAZING customer service. Our waiter Jeff was attentive, pleasant, engaging, and accommodating. The other staff in the restaurant were also nice and showed interest in our experience. The food was also great. The music was nice. My boyfriend and I can definitely see ourselves returning.

Upon arrival they check ID and temperature. You pay outside prior to entry due to covid. Advertised as $45 but after fees and 20% service charge it's $60. Food was delicious and freshly prepared, just one plate and a small dessert. No seconds on the food however bottomless mimosas made up for it. There is NO PARKING ON SUNDAY. AND NO VALET AVAILABLE DURING THE DAY. We had to drive around for about 20 min to find a spot and then walk back. That was very disappointing. They did still accept our reservation! That was exciting. The staff was buzzing around but seemed all business. Really great music selections. Our server was extremely attentive and friendly. I could tell she was smiling through the mask. It was nice to visit again to support the re-opening.

I am highly impressed and can not think of a place in the past that can compare. We've already decided that we will be back. We both decided on the lamb chops with asparagus. I had the mash and she substituted for the mac and cheese (somebodies momma is in that kitchen). The jerk wings were amazing as well and it came with a small portion of mac and cheese. If you're looking for a great atmosphere, Park is the place to be! Especially in the summer. Their brunch is amazing and you'll have a few options to choose from; buffet style. It's actually a tad bit cheaper than other places. The service is impeccable!

This might be the “littest” club I’ve been to in a while. On weekends they open up the top floor which adds up to 4 floors including an outdoor gazebo area. You can literally walk up and down all night without one boring moment. It’s so “lit” one time I walk thru each floor and just went home overwhelmed. This other time I drove 2.5 hours from Philly to spend a stack on bottles for my birthday. It’s not cheap but you will not be disappointed, ever...  There’s also like an army of security so it’s probably as safe as the White House down the street. If you spend a few bands on some bottles, they’ll bring out that Jumbotron with your name on it. Definitely worth it like once a year depending on your budget.

So first off, I am from the south. I love my good ol' southern cooking. Not only does The Park supply the BEST macaroni and cheese, chicken, chicken and waffles (brunch), greens, etc... but they do it with a very sophisticated twist. You truly get the 5 star experience here. Decor is nothing short of elegant.  Staffing is extremely warm and welcoming. Service is quick and dependable. The mimosas were WEAK and the buffet lines were long. This place is 4 levels and they only have one buffet set up. But the food was VERY good, which is why I'm still giving them 4 stars. The vibe was good as well. They're very strict on the 2 hour limit but many places are. Overall I wouldn't recommend it unless you really want the vibe.

Even though Park is a great club, this is more of a customer service review. I’m from DC & have been to clubs all throughout DC, whether it’s U Street, DuPont, Adams Morgan, etc & I’ve never seen or experienced a bouncer be as professional & nice as Charles (Asian guy) ! My sister’s a huge fan of Park so whenever she comes home, Park is her club of choice. So of course she wanted to celebrate her 29th bday there (Nov. 2). We arrived to Park around 10:30 & got next in line around 10:45. The group in front of us had a guy that was too drunk to get in & after a back & forth of trying to get him out of line once his friends left him, you could tell Charles’s mood was completely thrown off until someone else came out & tried to walk him onto the sidewalk. Now it’s about 10:50 & even though we were next in line, we jus knew they’d hold the line til 11 like most clubs do & cause us to pay for entry which we really didn’t wanna do since we preferred to spend that money on bday shots. So we told em it was her bday & showed him her id to prove it. He said “give me a second”, moved us to the side, smiled, wished her a happy bday & let us go in once they calmed the guy in front of us down. We were so happy he let us in, I jus had to ask him his name & told him I promised to write a review for him. I know I’m almost 3 weeks late Charles but I had to keep my word ! Park, pleaseee keep this man on your payroll because I love seeing him at the entrance whenever I go !

I will NEVER go back, the staff at The Park today compared to 2008 is complete trash! Aaron is still great but I would give this place 0 stars if I could!

I hadn’t been to The Park since I was in college, so arriving at the front door, I was feeling very familiar with what was about to happen: Remarkably nicely dressed-up people, expensive drinks, loud but good club music, and a packed house. Much to my surprise, The Park also has a menu (who knew that as a college kid? Lol) and the food is divine. More specifically, the ribeye steak is FANTASTIC. Cooked to perfection.  On the flip side: It bothered my friends that our waitress came by  and brought us water before our entire party arrived, but then never came back once everyone arrived. We had to tap random servers that passed by to order everything after the waters. And this is just a “me” thing: the music was SO LOUD. Staff and Manager are Rude and they will harass you if they don't like you. They have cameras in every corner(including bathrooms) recording you and your conversation without your  consent. I will not trust the cops at the entrance of Park, they work for the management so they stay loyal to management at Park regardless of your case. There are better places in DC to go to. If you want drama and get locked up for no reason then go to Park.

I recently went to the Park's Sunday Brunch/Day Party to celebrate a friends birthday. This was the first time I had come to their day party and after my experience, I will not be back. Upon arrival, there was a crowd of people just standing around the entrance. My party stood in this makeshift line for 10 minutes before the bouncers decided to tell everyone there were specific lines you needed to stand in to get inside. Even though we made a reservation, we had to stand in a 25+ person line in the cold and rain to get inside.  Once we made it to the front of the line after 30+ minutes, my bag was checked and I was denied entry due to a small mace I have on my key chain. I didn't think anything of it because it is for my protection and I had been to dinner at the Park before and there wasn't any bag check. The bouncer informed me that the only way I could enter was if I threw away my mace even after I offered to return it to my car and come back (if I did this, I would be forfeiting my entry to the 'establishment' and could not return that day). He claimed he also couldn't hold it until I left either because there was alcohol on the premises. Unless he planned on drinking while he was working, I don't understand how that was an issue. The whole situation was ridiculous.  Brunch was a buffet style, which would have been fine if they had a big enough space to accommodate all the people that were there, but they don't. Everyone was literally on top of each other trying to get food and and take their plates back to their seats. If you don't have a reservation, you have to stand around with your plate or just hangout at the bar, either of which makes the place even more crowded. We couldn't even fully enjoy our time there because our waitress was trying to rush us out before 5:30 to prepare for a bottle service table.  The only reason why this review has two stars is because the food and music were good. Sunday Brunch service is trash.

Good looking crowd. Great happy hour spot. If you're in the area go check them out. You won't be disappointed.

I recently went here for the New Years celebration and it was by far the worse experience ever. I purchased two VIP tickets in addition to valet parking and meal. This place is very costly with poor customer service. The food was not only disgusting but under cooked. I sent two of my meals back and it took so long for them to replace my order I decided to cancel my order to prevent self frustration. With it being New Years Eve, I graciously told my waiter I will continue my night without food. As the night continued i purchased a bottle of champagne to bring in the new year, as well as, preparation to propose to my girlfriend. As soon as I make the purchase I was stopped by security and was accused of attempting to use the bathroom in the middle of the club. Of course I thought he was joking because what idiot would want to do the in a club full of people. I informed the gentleman he must be mistaken and have me confused with someone else. He began to get loud with me and aggressively pushed me towards the stairs to leave. I find it to be ironic due to the fact that i just spent over $300 and now being forced to leave right before midnight. I asked to speak to the manager on duty and to review the security footage. I find it very shameful and shocking for a place who market their business on professionalism and sophistication, but their staff consist of ignorant people who don't have any form of common sense. At this point I have contacted management and starting the process to recoup my loss, as well as, address the situation that occurred. I dont not recommend this place to anybody. I have informed all of my professional colleagues and posted the unfortunate situation on my social media accounts. I hope by me sharing my experience will help others and prevent issues as such from occurring.

I have never been so poorly treated as I was at this establishment.  We purchased a private table to celebrate my 39th and my friends 34th birthday on 12/22/18.  One of our friends had to leave so my brother and I escorted her out to wait for an uber.  When we tried to go back inside we were told to wait. It was 1:40am, freezing! and our belongings including our coats were at our table.  I asked the gentleman outside why we are waiting?... there was no line, we had our wrist bands on and we purchased a table.  He was very rude and said: "because you have to wait!" He was letting other people go in as they walked up.  I was freezing, and again asked him why he was keeping us outside?  He then said we were "aggressive" and could not come back in.  The other men outside seemed to take direction from him.  We were kept outside freezing for 25 minutes until luckily a friend came looking for us. I have never in my life been treated so badly after spending so much money and for no apparent reason.  I believe this may have been discrimination (I am white).  Buyers beware!

TL; DR Park serves dinner, Filet Mignon and Grilled Shrimp were my favorites, If you get the Chocolate melt away cakes make sure to get it with ice cream, It's a CLUB so the music is very loud and there are a lot of people walking around while you eat, Service is good depending on who you get.  When my bestie invited me to dinner, of course I said yes!  After she told me it was at Park, I had to do a double take.  I didn't know this but Park is a restaurant and a club all in one!  It was definitely intimidating standing outside wearing jeans and a t-shirt while everyone else was dressed up like they were about to go clubbing at 6pm on a Thursday afternoon.  After the bouncer let me in and my bestie showed up, whom was dressed up (thanks for the memo), we sat down at a small table right behind the hostess desk.  The table looked liked like it could only hold a few drinks but surprisingly it held all the food that we had ordered.  We ordered the fried calamari, the sampler platter, and of course the key lime parfait, vanilla bean ice cream, and the chocolate melt away cakes.  The fried calamari came out piping hot yet it was delectably crispy.  The sample platter came out and it was a huge square place with 5 compartments for each of the items to sample.  The sample platter was made up of grilled shrimp, filet mignon, jerk chicken wings, blackend salmon with sweet corn bread, and baked macaroni & cheese.  My favorite from the sampler platter hands down was the Filet Mignon.  It was cooked the perfect medium rare on top of creamy mashed potatoes served with a red wine demi glaze.  My second favorite was the grilled shrimp, it was topped with a salty, tangy, sweet dressing that just complimented the smokey shrimp perfectly.  I heeded the advice of my waitress and got the vanilla ice cream with the chocolate melt away cakes and my goodness, it was the best decision I made that day.  The cakes were a bit bitter and warm so eating it with a scoop of ice cream gave was absolutely perfect.  You had the sweetness of the ice cream balancing out the bitterness of the chocolate cake and the ice cream is cold with a super warm/hot chocolate cake just made the experience magically delicious. The garnish of raspberries gave my taste buds a nice refresher after each cake.  Alone the cakes and ice cream weren't that great, but together, it's awesome!  If you like warm brownies with a scoop of ice cream, you'll like this! HIGHLY RECOMMEND TOGETHER.  BE WARNED: it is a club after all so the music is really loud and you will have to shout to talk to the person across from you.  There are a lot of people walking around with drinks in their hands either waiting around for a table or dancing.  GRATUITY is always included, even if you have a party of 2 or 6, it's already apart of the bill!  Service can be slow, but i think it's because the music is so loud, it takes a bit for the wait staff to hear people's order and such. Also the day that I went, there were only 2-3 waiters for all 8ish tables (only saw the tables in the front near the front door on the 1st level)  Overall the food was surprisingly good and our waitress was awesome!  Having dinner at park was definitely a very unique and enjoyable dining experience.  I would come back for dinner but request a table that isn't stationed right in the middle of the walkway.

I ordered the Jerk chicken and Macaroni and Cheese, which I had heard so much about, and the ppl stand corrected....it was bomb.....😊 The server was excellent and the atmosphere was great. Since I had a dinner reservation late in the evening, I stayed for the club which was not a let down. There are 3 floors with DJ's  playing top hits, old and new. Overall, I would go back again.

I have been going to the Park for quite some years now, I'll say about 7 years. It's my favorite spot because it has my two favorite bartenders in the District Eddy and Neil. This past weekend I received an email from I believe one their promoters/workers about an event on Monday afternoon. I followed the prompt and signed up for. Basically the email said you will receive two premium drinks and access to the buffet. I would like to add that I'm doing pretty well for myself thanks GOD. I arrived at the door right after 5pm and the bouncer told me straight up I don't anything about this it's $20 for the long line and $40 for the short one to get in. He didn't even give me chance to show him the info. As I stated above I'm a regular at the Park because I know personally a lot of their staff including Pierre. But this past Monday was way below the expectations because they had an attitude like you're there for freebies. I paid the $40, went in looking for someone in charge. They directed me to a light skinned gentleman, bald head, a little heavy set probably in his late 40s mid 50s. I wanted to understand if that email was a scam because it had all the info of the Park and it was on Event brite as well. He told me exactly this , there's nothing I can do for you have to pay to get in and here's a good card. I was speechless. Regardless of my expensive outfit and jewelry he just handed to me that stupid card for food like that's why I approached him. I will do my best to have a one on one with their upper management because that's unacceptable. They became a bit cocky and we can't let that happen because it will eventually ruin the reputation of the only good spot we have in the District.
